A RAPE victim is gatvol after cops arrested and released a rape suspect without him even appearing in court. The 29-year-old woman from Makhaza in Khayelitsha said she was attacked by a man on Monday, 2 May, who dragged her to his shack while she was unconscious. The woman told the SunTeam that the man allegedly raped her all night in the presence of two of his friends. “He told them they could rape me if they wanted to but they covered their heads with a blanket and slept,” she said. She managed to escape in the morning and reported the matter to the Harare cops in Khayelitsha. The man was arrested but failed to appear in court on 10 May. But she later saw him walking on the street. When he was supposed to appear in court, the suspect wasn’t there. Cops told her had an infection on his foot and would appear the following day. She went the next day but once again he wasn’t there. The family went to the cop shop again where the suspect was rearrested apparently for a different rape incident. “I’m told he was rearrested for another rape case. If he didn’t have another case were they going to re-arrest him?,” asked the victim.  I’m very angry at the cops for what they did to me,” she said. Cops spokesman Captain Frederick van Wyk said the man was bust. “ he case is being investigated by Khayelitsha FCS Unit. The investigation continues,” he said. confirmed the incident and said the man was bust. “The 27 year old suspect was arrested on a charge of rape on 9 May after he allegedly raped a 29 year old female in Makhaza on 4 May. The suspect was released, however he was re-arrested on another rape charge for which he appeared in the Khayelitsha Magistrate Court on 13 May. The cases are running concurrently in court. The dockets are currently still at court and no new court date is available. The case is being investigated by Khayelitsha FCS Unit. The investigation continues,” Van Wyk said.